Title : [Respiratory failure during the course of congenital myopathy effectively treated with nocturnal noninvasive nasal positive pressure ventilation].
Date : 2000
Publication_type : Journal Article
Abstract : Respiratory muscle weakness in myopathy may result in respiratory failure. 41 year old male with congenital myopathy was successfully treated with nocturnal noninvasive nasal positive pressure ventilation. NPPV resulted in improvement of arterial blood gases and allowed to close tracheostomy. Patient was able to return to full time employment.
